Iranian Revolutionary Guards fired warning shots across the bridge of a US-flagged cargo ship in the Strait of Hormuz on April 24 . 
  The Maersk Tigris was seized for trespassing and 34 sailors were on board . 
  The Pentagon said the incident raised concerns about the security of shipping lanes in the region . 
  Iranian sources said they seized the cargo ship after a legal dispute . 
  On April 24 the Revolutionary Guards 'harassed' a US cargo ship . 
  Four days later Iranian patrol boats boarded the cargo vessel and seized it . 
  Pentagon said it was the same ship that was 'harassing' the US ship . 
